Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
flattenIlm(25.10)                                            flattenIlm(25.10)

Name
       flattenIlm  -  Flattens  the  interface  logic models (ILMs) at the top
       level so that the entire design can be analyzed at the top

Syntax
       flattenIlm

       [-help]

       Flattens the interface logic models (ILMs) at the top level so that the
       entire design can be analyzed at the top. When you  use  this  command,
       the software switches from blackbox view to ILM view.

       If  you  do  not run flattenIlm, the ILM netlist will not be visible to
       the Innovus software. You can switch  between  the  ILM  view  and  the
       blackbox view using the flattenIlm and unflattenIlm commands.

       All  super  commands  such  as  timeDesign, place_design, and optDesign
       flatten the ILMs internally and hence no  explicit  flattenILM  is  re-
       quired.  However,  you should use this command for other timing related
       commands. For example, for the report_timing command, you need  to  run
       flattenILM  before  reporting  timing. It would not work in the unflat-
       tened mode.

       Example:

       flattenIlm

       report_timing

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the usage of the flat-
              tenIlm command.

Related Information
              * optDesign

              * place_design,

              * report_timing

              * timeDesign

